reviews.text: I come to Pho Midway 1-2 times a week for lunch! I have had a lot from the menu, but the P1 Pho is my go to. The service is great and food always comes out very quickly. I would recommend it to anyone if you want authentic, affordable and delicious Vietnamese.

Walked in and stood at the register for 5 minutes while the owner and (I assume) his daughter carried on a conversation. No greeting, no eye contact‚Äînothing. A couple walked in after me and were immediately welcomed with smiles and energy. Only then did someone glance at me and say, ‚ÄúOh yes, welcome to you too.‚Äù

Waited 10 minutes for my food, which would‚Äôve been fine‚Äîif I hadn‚Äôt walked out and seen not one, not two, but FOUR dead cockroaches right by the front door.

If that‚Äôs what‚Äôs visible to customers, I don‚Äôt want to imagine what‚Äôs behind the counter.

The food here is decent, but my experience with the bun bo hue was disappointing. While the flavor was good, the rice noodles were mostly chopped/tore into very small, 1 to 2 cm pieces. I've never had this happen at any other pho restaurant before.

By far some of the best pho I‚Äôve ever had. Very well seasoned and tasty even before you place your extras in. The service and the food were over the top. I will definitely be traveling from Frisco more often. This meal put me in a food coma afterwards.

The food was quite good‚Äîboth the pho and the fried rice were flavorful and satisfying. However, the service left a lot to be desired. I ordered one bowl of pho with two types of meat and a fried rice, and even double-checked with the server to make sure the order was correct. She confirmed it, but when the food arrived, there were two bowls of pho.

When I politely pointed out the mistake, she sighed right in front of me, even though it was her error. Later, when I asked for an extra plate, she sighed again with a strange facial expression that made the interaction uncomfortable.

Good food, but the unprofessional service really took away from the experience.

editorial_summary.overview: Bowls of pho & other Vietnamese cuisine presented in a classic, modest setting with counter seating.

detailedReviews.text:
I decided to give this place a try despite a friend telling me it was just ‚ÄúOK.‚Äù Unfortunately, he was right‚Äîbut the issues go far beyond the food.

The restaurant was disorganized and the service was poor. I placed a to-go order in an almost empty restaurant, with only one other person dining in. I tipped the default 20%, assuming the experience would go smoothly. It didn‚Äôt.

My order was brought out and left next to a larger to-go order without any notification. After waiting 25 minutes, I asked for an update, and the staff found my order‚Äîsitting there the whole time. Cold.

There‚Äôs a small sign on the counter that reads ‚ÄúRing for Help,‚Äù which honestly reflects the overall attitude: customer service is clearly not a priority. The space itself was dirty and looked run-down. Not what you‚Äôd expect or hope for in a dining experience.

As for the food‚Äîmediocre at best, especially cold. The herbs weren‚Äôt washed properly, and the protein portions were small despite ordering a large.

There are far better options in town that are just a short drive away. I won‚Äôt be returning.

Update to review below.

I got a to-go order at Midway Pho and my Deluxe Pho was perfect spice and the portions of the ingredients was perfect.   My order of Beef Stew came with little to no meat, only one piece of a large clump of fat was included (and it had *hints* of beef on it).  I was very  disappointed because the broth was so flavorful.  If I were in the store, I don't feel like they would have done me like this.

Edit to my review based on response received  from restaurant ‚Ä¶

The description of my meal was this :

Flavorful simmered beef broth and TENDER BEEF CUBES with daikon and carrot‚Ä¶

I received ZERO meat other than the small amounts attached to the beef tendon ( which was not listed in the description ). The person preparing the dish provided almost zero meat in the ‚Äústew‚Äù.   I cut open the tendon to eat as much meat as possible but I felt like Tiny Tim‚Äôs family when they were shaving the bean into portions.

detailedReviews.author: Ashten Alexander
detailedReviews.text:
Sorry for the lengthy review.....BUT
Oh, man! If I could give this place a 10 out of 10, I absolutely would. This is hands-down the BEST pho I've ever tasted. My partner and I love it so much that we come at least once a week--it's become a bit of a tradition for us!

The experience isn't just about the food, though. The owner and his family are incredibly warm and welcoming, and they truly make you feel like a part of their extended family. We were lucky enough to chat with the owner one evening, and he shared a bit of the restaurant's backstory with us. He mentioned that it took them years to perfect the broth, and I can tell--they absolutely nailed it. Hearing about his journey was a treat; he's laid-back, super friendly, and clearly passionate about the food he serves.

The establishment itself is always spotless--something I really appreciate. You can tell they take pride in maintaining a clean, inviting space for their guests. Now, onto the star of the show: the pho. Oh my goodness! I always order the pho with no meat, spice level 3, in a small bowl. Every time, the flavors blow me away. The broth is rich and aromatic, with just the right amount of spice that warms you up without overpowering the other ingredients. The balance of flavors is incredible--it's comforting, fresh, and so satisfying. This bowl of pho is simply a little slice of heaven.
